OL,3,CFears poorest families won't be able
OL,4,Cto use free childcare proposal
OL,6,F"A lot of mothers now want to return
OL,7,Fto work, and it's the only way they
OL,8,Fpossibly see it as an option".
OL,10,FShe explained that her grandchild goes
OL,11,Fto nursery two and a half hours a
OL,12,Fweek, which costs as much as the
OL,13,Fmortgage.
OL,15,F"Childcare is very expensive, but
OL,16,Fsocially, it's really good for them to
OL,17,Fmix with other children".
OL,19,FFamilies in Jersey pay approximately
OL,20,F#21,600 per year for full-time
OL,21,Fchildcare.
